accessibility.text: Work “on” the organization, not just “in” it.
Most people work in their orgs without working on them.
Work “on” the organization, not just “in” it.
Most people work in their orgs without working on them.
Working “on” the organization is about changing the structure of circles and roles to refine what we can expect of each other.

Most people work in their orgs without working on them.
Working “on” the organization is about changing the structure of circles and roles to refine what we can expect of each other.
Changing the structure is how organizations learn.
If you don’t do this work, you are robbing the organization of learning.
